                <mxCell id="25" value="2.private contructor: -&amp;nbsp; When the class constructor is private, this means we cannot create instance for that class&lt;div&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#ffffff&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;We can also define class structure with anonymous static method with will be executed as soon as the class object is registered,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" parent="23" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry y="60" width="370" height="90" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="114" value="2.private contructor: -&amp;nbsp; When our code within the class is like this that we don&#39;t need to create any instance from that class, the we can make that class constructor a private constructor&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Like when all the properties in our class are static" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" vertex="1" parent="23">
                    <mxGeometry y="150" width="370" height="80" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="52" value="3. Multiple constructor: -" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" vertex="1" parent="23">
