                    </mxGeometry>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="108" value="1. Constructor: - by the name only we can understand that the it constructs the structure of the instance, based on how the constructor is defined in the class" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" vertex="1" parent="107">
                    <mxGeometry y="30" width="370" height="70" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="113" value="2. This constructor funciton alway runs, when we initialized/create any instance.&lt;div&gt;So we can also defined some code logic in constructor that we want to perfrom before any instance initialization&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" vertex="1" parent="107">
